node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

Midnight sun magic in Senja via @seffis. ☀️ Check out his glorious adventures with @jonathan_priskorn in Norway, where the sun doesn't set!

Usually occurring in the Senja region from the end of May 'til the end of July, the sublime "midnight sun" is an experience you won't forget. A natural phenomenon in the Arctic Circle and Antarctic Circle, the midnight sun occurs during the height of summer. During this period, you can see the sun at the local time of midnight, which means it never gets dark. 

Have you experienced the midnight sun? 🕛

📽 @seffis
🚶‍♂️ @jonathan_priskorn
📍 Senja, Norway
🎶 Whips and Chainz - Benni5stax

Marveling at @withluke's awe-inspiring captures of Mt. Fuji, one of the most iconic landmarks of Japan known for its graceful conical form. 🗻

Whatever the season may be, Jeju Island is a sought-after destination for its stunning beaches and relaxed atmosphere. But if you'd like to spot hydrangeas blossoming, it's best to visit from June to July when chances are extremely high. During this time, visitors and locals alike can enjoy hydrangeas in shades of blue, purple, and pink. 💐

Have you been to Jeju Island in South Korea yet? What else should we do when on the island? 🇰🇷

node.text:
Taking a dip with @lorenz.weisse via @_fabiozingg at Lac Bleu, a stunning mountain lake known for its vivid turquoise waters—the color of which is caused by the combination of algae and glacial clay. 💎

There are several picnic tables around the lake, making the destination ideal for a quick nature getaway. Though the body of water is small, it's nonetheless superb, attracting adventure seekers of all kinds. Whether you visit during the summer or winter, you'll surely be blown away by the landscape's beauty.

Have you been to an alpine lake in Switzerland? Which one is your favorite? 🇨🇭

📽 @_fabiozingg
🏊‍♂️ @lorenz.weisse 
📍 Lac Bleu, Arolla, Switzerland
🎶 In This Shirt - The Irrepressibles

node.text:
Staying slacky with @yehslacks in Malibu, California. Would you take it to the extreme and try this out? 🤯

Slacklining is a sport and art that mixes balance training, recreation, and moving meditation. Though similar practices may have been observed previously, slacklining evolved in the 1980s at Yosemite Valley, where a pair of climbers introduced the activity to the climber's camps in the valley.

From there, it slowly spread within the climbing scene and eventually became a sport for daredevils all over the world. 🔥 

🤸‍♀️ @yehslacks
📽 @recklessbenschneider
📍 Malibu, California
🎶 Heart Of Glass (Live from the iHeart Music Festival) - Miley Cyrus

Venturing into Botswana with @safari.frank, where we can catch this superb sighting of a lion family, otherwise known as a 'pride'. 🦁

While many big cats choose to live alone, lions are incredibly sociable and live together in a group called pride. This incredible footage was shot in Chobe National Park, Botswana's first national park that's also known to be the most biologically diverse in the country. Featuring a variety of wildlife and lush vegetation, the park undoubtedly leaves its guests with a stronger appreciation for nature.

Have you experienced a safari adventure yet and would you add this place to your bucket list? 🇧🇼

📽 @safari.frank
📍 Chobe National Park, Botswana
🎶 Circle Of Life - Carmen Twillie, Lebo M.

Leisurely roaming around the Scottish Highlands with @theslowtraveler. 😌 Offering blissful seclusion and majestic scenery, this northern part of Scotland is a favorite of outdoorsy travelers and photographers. Notably, it has no shortage of beautiful castles, dramatic landscapes, and tranquil areas where you can achieve genuine solitude. 🍃

Do you love slow-paced getaways? 💭 If you are from Scotland, tell us about the must-visit places here!

📽 @theslowtraveler
📍 Scottish Highlands, Scotland

An epic view to wake up to via @julietpisner. 🏕 This glorious scenery can be found at the Inyo National Forest tucked in California's beautiful Eastern Sierra. ☀️

The name "Inyo" comes from a Native American word, which means "dwelling place of the great spirit." The forest is home to the Ancient Bristlecone Pine Forest, which features the oldest living trees in the world. 🌲 If you'd love to explore the forest, you may go camping, picnicking, and hiking in the area, among other recreational activities.

Would you camp out here? What are your favorite camping spots in the USA?

📽 @julietpisner
